I"<p>Surprisingly, among the thousands of religions which have been invented and <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/migration-lineage-correlates-with-novelty-seeking-genes">adopted throughout the history of humanity</a>, patterns arise. Early desert cultures had monotheistic religions, while rain forest dwellers mostly had polytheistic ones (presumably reflecting the myriad of species observed). <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/organism-and-ecology-are-codetermined">The ecology influences adopted</a> religions.</p>
